Study.StudyHelp:
This one is testing a Kids’ meal bag vs. the post wave a box, so we’ll be especially interested in any comments about the packaging, or how the contents were affected by the packaging.
Chick-fil-A is planning to refresh the Kid’s Meal experience. One of the ways to achieve this is by refreshing the packaging from the current bag to a sturdier box. Chick-fil-A wants to test the new Kid’s Meal box in restaurants to get feedback from Customers and are particularly interested to see if the Kid’s Meal Box offers a better Customer experience than the current bag. Customer feedback from 30 free-standing stores within the Charlotte, NC market is sought. • This research will provide input into approval for chainwide rollout in Q1 of 2026 • To be considered for launch:  Kid’s Meals in the new box perform better than current on: • Overall Kid’s Meal Satisfaction • Satisfaction with Kid’s Meal Packaging  Kid’s Meals in the new box perform at parity or better than current on: • Kid’s Meal Reorder Intent • Kid’s Meal Value • Quality Consistent with Chick-fil-A
